5000|$|Carriages {{and coaches}} {{began to be}} widely used in Britain during the 17th century. However, real {{progress}} in carriage building was not made until the late 18th century, when Royal Mail coach service began. For the first time many carriages were designed for comfort and speed and were made alike, using <b>interchangeable</b> parts. Soon <b>carriage</b> driving became the fashionable way to travel, although for many years the cost of vehicles restricted their use primarily to the nobility and upper classes.|$|R

